For each odd $L_{3}$, the sum $L_{3}+1$ is even. However, for each odd $L_{2}$, the sum $L_{2}+2$ is odd. To still get an even digit in the tens place in the result, there must be a carry-over from the units place. Therefore, $L_{3}$ can only be 9.

For each odd $L_{1}$, the sum $L_{1}+4$ is odd. For the result to have an even digit in the hundreds place, there must be a carry-over from the tens place. Therefore, $L_{2}$ can only be 9 or 7.

